No.

33
00:04:19,842 --> 00:04:21,386
No, don't think about it.

34
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,472
I've already given up.

35
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:27,058
I can never date Kyung-seok.

36
00:04:31,771 --> 00:04:34,232
I don't want my life to get ruined again.

37
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,009
Did something happen?

38
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:02,927
You seem upset.

39
00:05:05,013 --> 00:05:06,180
There's no alcohol.

40
00:05:09,642 --> 00:05:11,436
Oh, I noticed you didn't clean today.

41
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:13,688
I did it for you, so you better
clean well from tomorrow.

42
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:16,899
I'll just pay the full rent
going forward,

43
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:19,402
so let's divide the housework.

44
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:25,992
I guess your part-time job
pays you well.

45
00:05:31,622 --> 00:05:33,291
What's with him?

46
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:47,930
We're friends, right?

47
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:51,768
I really think of you just as a friend.

48
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:54,395
100 percent.

49
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:17,960
What's wrong?

50
00:06:18,503 --> 00:06:20,380
What? Oh no, it's nothing.

51
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:25,093
What am I going to do
if I run into him?

52
00:06:26,386 --> 00:06:27,637
What am I supposed to say?

53
00:06:28,846 --> 00:06:31,432
-Hey, it's a special lecture.
-It must be held by Kelun.

54
00:06:31,516 --> 00:06:33,976
-Where's the lecture held at?
-It doesn't say it there.

55
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:37,063
Does that mean we can meet
Ms. Na Hye-sung in person?

56
00:06:37,397 --> 00:06:38,398
I'm so excited.

57
00:06:38,564 --> 00:06:39,649
It sounds fun.

58
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,776
I'm glad I didn't enroll
in summer classes.

59
00:06:42,026 --> 00:06:44,028
Do you think Woo-young
will be attending as well?

60
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:47,657
If you like him so much,
you should dress up like me.

61
00:06:48,324 --> 00:06:49,867
That's not my true self.

62
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:52,787
I don't want to seduce him
by faking myself.

63
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:53,704
Seduce?

64
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:55,164
Did you just say seduce?

65
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:58,126
That word doesn't suit you at all.

66
00:06:58,876 --> 00:06:59,710
Hey!

67
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:03,756
-Did you put up a banner for me?
-Of course.

68
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:05,341
It's a special lecture by you.

69
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,010
I didn't think I'd be nervous.

70
00:07:08,302 --> 00:07:10,054
But I am now that I'm here.

71
00:07:14,642 --> 00:07:15,643
Are you going to sing?

72
00:07:16,727 --> 00:07:17,687
Will they make me sing?

73
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:20,189
Sure, kids these days are difficult
to deal with.

74
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:24,152
That actually made me
pull myself together.

75
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:26,195
I wish you good luck.

76
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:30,741
What should I do?

77
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:36,414
Are you sure Woo-young is coming?

78
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:39,667
Gosh, stop talking about him.
I'm sure he'll be here.

79
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:55,433
A SCENT THAT WILL MAKE
PEOPLE REMEMBER YOU.

80
00:07:56,976 --> 00:08:00,271
I guess the power of genetics is
really incredible.

81
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:03,649
My mother-in-law's so pretty.

82
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:06,569
Since when did she become
your mother-in-law?

83
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:10,907
Since today?

84
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:15,369
I can see where Kyung-seok got
his looks from.

85
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:20,041
His mom's beautiful but Kyung-seok isn't
that good looking.

86
00:08:20,833 --> 00:08:23,461
Frankly, he and I are pretty much
on the same level. We're both tall.

87
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:26,380
Do you have any conscience at all?

88
00:08:31,552 --> 00:08:34,305
I'm sure you all know who she is
but I'll still introduce her to you.

89
00:08:34,388 --> 00:08:37,225
She's a proud graduate of Hankook
University's chemistry department

90
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:39,185
and CEO of Kelun Korea.
She's Ms. Na Hye-sung.

91
00:08:43,231 --> 00:08:45,691
I'm glad to meet you all.
My name is Na Hye-sung.

92
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:54,450
Where's Kyung-seok?

93
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:58,663
His mom came to school to give a lecture
but he's not even here.

94
00:09:05,336 --> 00:09:07,588
Our manager desperately waited
for you to come

95
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:10,383
but he went to a seminar abroad.

96
00:09:11,217 --> 00:09:14,011
I might not be as good as him,
but can I still give it a try?

97
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:16,556
I don't care as long as you pay me.

98
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,975
Thank you for trusting me.

99
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:20,685
Do I get paid right away?

100
00:09:20,768 --> 00:09:24,605
Of course, you'll get paid
as soon as you're done. Let's begin.

101
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:30,528
You have a girlfriend, right?

102
00:09:30,611 --> 00:09:32,905
I hope she'll like it.

103
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:36,367
But then, I don't think it matters
since you're so handsome.

104
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:39,704
Even an afro would look like
a fashion trend if you do it.

105
00:09:42,873 --> 00:09:48,838
What I meant was a person's look
is what completes the hairstyle.

106
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:52,383
I won't do an afro on you.
I'm not out of my mind.

107
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:54,885
Perfume always comes last.

108
00:09:55,636 --> 00:09:56,804
Let me explain.

109
00:09:56,887 --> 00:09:59,515
When you get ready to go out,
you put on your clothes, do your hair,

110
00:09:59,599 --> 00:10:00,725
and put makeup on.

111
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:04,020
And no one puts on perfume
before doing any of those things.

112
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:07,023
However, there are times when this
invisible last step

113
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:09,859
ends up lingering in people's memories
for a long time.

114
00:10:09,942 --> 00:10:14,405
It's hard to remember a certain person's
hairstyle or outfit from long time ago.

115
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:16,991
But you remember their smell.

116
00:10:17,074 --> 00:10:19,827
That smell stays in your head
along with that person's image.

117
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,375
This is yours, right?

118
00:10:28,294 --> 00:10:29,629
You can wear that perfume.

119
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:34,842
When you smell the steam
from a rice cooker,

120
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:37,303
you're reminded of your mother.

121
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:40,389
And when you smell the perfume
you used to wear a long time ago,

122
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:43,225
you're reminded
of how you used to feel back then.

123
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:48,397
I'm not sure how you'll remember me...

124
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:01,285
Isn't that Kyung-seok?

125
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:04,664
I have to say, he likes to put himself
in the spotlight.

126
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:26,227
I don't know how you'll remember me
after this lecture.

127
00:11:26,310 --> 00:11:29,021
-Don't ever dye your hair like him.
-But I hope...

128
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,315
-It doesn't look good on him.
-...you'll at least remember

129
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:33,734
what I told you all about scent today.

130
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:38,364
If you wish to take part in our company
program, please submit applications.

131
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,700
I'll end my lecture here.

132
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:53,254
-Thank you for the lecture.
-Thank you.

133
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,720
-Your finals are coming up, right?
-Yes.

134
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:03,139
Is everything okay?

135
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:04,807
What do you mean?

136
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:06,934
Well...

137
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:11,105
What's your plan for the summer?
Are you going to apply for the program?

138
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:13,899
I'll think about it.

139
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:17,027
Okay, but I hope you do apply.

140
00:12:20,656 --> 00:12:21,490
See you.

141
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:29,248
Is he going through late adolescence?

142
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:31,459
What's up with him?

143
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,713
Girls get their hair done after
they go through a break up.

144
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:37,715
I wonder if it's something similar.

145
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:45,723
I'm sorry.

146
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:55,191
You dyed your hair.

147
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:58,611
Yes.

148
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:02,740
-It looks pretty.
-I didn't do it to look pretty.

149
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:05,701
Oh, sorry. It looks good.

150
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:07,161
I didn't do it to look good.

151
00:13:07,828 --> 00:13:08,662
Oh really?

152
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:11,957
-I guess you just did it for no reason.
-Not exactly.

153
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:15,753
Well, okay.

154
00:13:16,545 --> 00:13:18,964
I'll go now. Good luck on your finals.

155
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:24,220
Why did I say good luck?
The exams haven't even started yet.

156
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:26,263
This is driving me crazy.

157
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:32,561
Is  he getting ready to become
a celebrity?

158
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:34,313
With his personality?

159
00:13:34,814 --> 00:13:36,941
What's wrong with Kyung-seok's
personality?

160
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:39,485
It's not normal.

161
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,111
He'll never do as he's told.

162
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:43,823
With Kyung-seok's good looks

163
00:13:44,114 --> 00:13:46,283
his manager will listen
to Kyung-seok's orders.

164
00:13:47,952 --> 00:13:50,538
Do you still like Kyung-seok?

165
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:54,917
To be honest,

166
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:57,419
I gave up on him.

167
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,213
I gave up.

168
00:14:01,924 --> 00:14:05,094
But he's too good-looking
to erase from my heart.

169
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:09,765
I know you guys all have a small crush
on him as well.

170
00:14:10,599 --> 00:14:11,475
Am I wrong?

171
00:14:26,699 --> 00:14:29,910
Be honest with me.
My cooking was terrible, right?

172
00:14:33,789 --> 00:14:35,499
You can be honest with me.

173
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:38,711
No, it wasn't that bad.

174
00:14:40,671 --> 00:14:43,799
By the way, Kyung-hee.
Will you take a look at this?

175
00:14:49,471 --> 00:14:50,931
-Is that Kyung-seok?
-Yes.

176
00:14:51,765 --> 00:14:53,642
I didn't want to sound too nagging

177
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:55,811
so I couldn't ask why he dyed his hair.

178
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:58,939
He's not the type who cares about
his looks.

179
00:14:59,523 --> 00:15:00,941
What's wrong with him?

180
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:04,069
-Maybe he's dating someone.
-Do you think so?

181
00:15:04,695 --> 00:15:07,865
Or maybe, he got his heart broken
by someone.

182
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:11,994
By whom?

183
00:15:19,501 --> 00:15:20,336
Thanks.

184
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:23,130
Write me a receipt.

185
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:27,384
You said a verbal agreement
wouldn't be effective.

186
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:30,304
I see that you've got used to
life in society now.

187
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:33,766
-Didn't I say I learn things quickly?
-It's partly thanks to my useful tips.

188
00:15:33,849 --> 00:15:35,851
It's not cool to take credit like that.

189
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:40,814
-How cool of you.
-Aren't you writing me a receipt?

190
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:50,324
Did you do modeling for a hair salon?

191
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:52,618
How did you know?

192
00:15:53,202 --> 00:15:55,162
I told you. I've done
almost every part-time job.

193
00:15:55,245 --> 00:15:56,330
DO KYUNG-SEOK HAS PAID

194
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:58,791
I thought you wouldn't do such a thing
with your personality.

195
00:15:58,874 --> 00:16:00,751
Did you not like doing chores?

196
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:04,046
Or is there a change in your mind?

197
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:10,511
Don't act like you know about me.

198
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,912
He changed his hair color again.

199
00:18:26,021 --> 00:18:27,856
I got this question wrong.

200
00:18:28,065 --> 00:18:31,110
Finals are finally over!

201
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:37,491
Hey, finals are over.
How about we go play games?

202
00:18:37,616 --> 00:18:39,409
Sure, let's get it.

203
00:18:39,868 --> 00:18:40,828
Let's go.

204
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:43,163
It's over.

205
00:18:44,123 --> 00:18:46,125
Why don't we go eat something good?

206
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:48,919
Let's not eat near the school.
I want to go somewhere far.

207
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:51,004
Let's go.

208
00:18:58,512 --> 00:18:59,972
Hello, Ms. Na.

209
00:19:01,723 --> 00:19:03,892
Yes, I'm done with my finals.

210
00:19:07,646 --> 00:19:08,480
Okay.

211
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:11,483
Did I gain weight?

212
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:14,486
I ate too much because
I was stressed with finals.

213
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:16,238
No, you didn't.

214
00:19:16,738 --> 00:19:18,574
You say that all the time.

215
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:19,616
How was the exam?

216
00:19:20,826 --> 00:19:21,994
-Hello.
-Hi.

217
00:19:22,578 --> 00:19:25,831
About going on a field trip
to Kyung-seok mom's company,

218
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:27,666
are there senior applicants?

219
00:19:28,292 --> 00:19:30,377
-Not that I know of.
-Is that so?

220
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,881
-It might be quite awkward then.
-Are you going to apply?

221
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:36,550
Never mind.

222
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:38,302
It wouldn't look good for me to be there.

223
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,139
Are you still mad?

224
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:44,433
My goodness.

225
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,894
-See you later.
-Bye.

226
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,023
-What did you just do?
-What?

227
00:19:51,398 --> 00:19:53,400
Don't you know that he said
I was a fatty?

228
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:55,402
How could you talk to him
like nothing happened?

229
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,946
It's not like I'm never going
to see him again.

230
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:01,783
Kyung-seok turned him into a mop.

231
00:20:02,367 --> 00:20:04,995
Even classmates care for each other.
What's wrong with you?

232
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:07,080
Tae-hee.

233
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:10,375
Tae-hee, let's go eat something good.

234
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:12,377
Tae...

235
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,504
Gosh, this is tiring.

236
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:25,098
Dong-won, you must've been really hungry.

237
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:29,311
Sorry I couldn't take care of you
because I was busy with finals.

238
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:31,855
Is it good?

239
00:20:37,819 --> 00:20:38,987
Hello, Dong-won.

240
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:43,825
Guys, I think

241
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:46,328
the beauty in my department
really has a crush on me.

242
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:48,247
That's only your delusion.

243
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:53,543
No, I'm telling you.
The name of her cat is same as my name.

244
00:20:54,336 --> 00:20:56,838
Maybe your name is Nabi or Kitty.

245
00:20:57,381 --> 00:20:59,383
It's rarely used to name a cat.

246
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:00,592
It's for people.

247
00:21:01,510 --> 00:21:02,886
Can this be a coincidence?

248
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,806
Can you still say that
she doesn't like me?

249
00:21:13,814 --> 00:21:16,024
It must've been hard
studying for your finals.

250
00:21:16,108 --> 00:21:16,942
Eat up.

251
00:21:17,776 --> 00:21:19,069
Thank you.

252
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,323
Let me do it.

253
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:25,701
Moms usually do this for you.

254
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:27,119
You should start eating.

255
00:21:28,245 --> 00:21:29,705
Thank you.

256
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:36,128
By the way, didn't you want to say
something to me?

257
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:41,508
Actually, I have a question.

258
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:46,221
Nothing special has happened
to Kyung-seok, right?

259
00:21:49,766 --> 00:21:52,436
No, I don't think so.

260
00:21:54,062 --> 00:21:55,814
Then why did he dye his hair?

261
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:58,900
Kyung-hee told me he doesn't care
about his looks.

262
00:21:59,526 --> 00:22:01,528
I'm not too sure about that,

263
00:22:02,112 --> 00:22:04,489
but he dyed his hair back to black.

264
00:22:04,573 --> 00:22:05,449
Really?

265
00:22:06,616 --> 00:22:10,329
I was worried I might look nosy
if I asked him about it directly.

266
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:12,873
I see.

267
00:22:17,919 --> 00:22:20,505
I guess you're the one in trouble.

268
00:22:21,798 --> 00:22:22,632
Pardon?

269
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:25,010
Are you worried about something?

270
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:34,227
I guess you don't want to share.

271
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:35,604
I'm sorry.

272
00:22:36,396 --> 00:22:37,356
That's not it.

273
00:22:40,525 --> 00:22:41,860
The thing is...

274
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:46,865
TA, I want to apply for the field trip.

275
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,116
Okay.

276
00:22:51,745 --> 00:22:53,747
LIST OF FIELD TRIP APPLICANTS

277
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:56,500
-You're Hyun Sua, right?
-Yes.

278
00:22:58,460 --> 00:23:02,839
KO YE-NA, KIM TAE-HEE, YOO EUN,
JANG WON-HO, KIM SUNG-WUN...

279
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:04,925
It's done.

280
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:07,761
Thank you. Goodbye.

281
00:23:07,844 --> 00:23:08,678
Bye.

282
00:23:11,056 --> 00:23:13,141
Kyung-seok, are you here to apply for...

283
00:23:17,896 --> 00:23:18,730
What's wrong?

284
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:21,483
Don't tell me you're here
to call off the rent issue.

285
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:23,735
I'm here to apply for the field trip.

286
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:25,821
-To Kelun?
-Yes.

287
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:34,496
-Do better for your mom.
-That's my business.

288
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:40,419
Are you mad at me?

289
00:23:43,713 --> 00:23:45,549
I'm done, right? Bye.

290
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:54,558
I can't read his mind.

291
00:24:00,647 --> 00:24:01,815
You like him,

292
00:24:01,898 --> 00:24:05,193
and he seems to like you too.
Why do you have to give up?

293
00:24:08,321 --> 00:24:10,824
I think I'm scared.

294
00:24:14,244 --> 00:24:16,413
He's beyond my league.

295
00:24:17,414 --> 00:24:18,707
He's too perfect for me.

296
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,625
Still, you two like each other.
So why?

297
00:24:23,795 --> 00:24:25,213
The thing is,

298
00:24:26,423 --> 00:24:28,633
a girl who's really pretty
has a crush on him.

299
00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:32,012
Everyone thinks
that they'd make a good couple.

300
00:24:33,346 --> 00:24:37,350
As you know, I got plastic surgery
all over my face.

301
00:24:38,351 --> 00:24:41,146
If he dates me, what will people say?
I'm just too scared.

302
00:24:41,897 --> 00:24:42,939
I see.

303
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,526
I'm so stupid, right?

304
00:24:50,197 --> 00:24:51,031
But still,

305
00:24:51,907 --> 00:24:54,201
what matters is the fact that you two
like each other.

306
00:24:54,284 --> 00:24:56,244
So don't think about other people.

307
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:01,583
That's what everyone else will say though.

308
00:25:03,210 --> 00:25:04,252
I understand.

309
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:07,672
I'm sure many girls would feel
that way in your situation.

310
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:13,762
I'm so mad at the people that made you
think that way.

311
00:25:15,805 --> 00:25:19,559
I don't know the details,
so I can't really give you advice.

312
00:25:19,935 --> 00:25:23,146
But perhaps, that pretty girl...

313
00:25:23,980 --> 00:25:27,567
isn't much different from you.

314
00:25:28,944 --> 00:25:32,906
I just don't want you
to have regrets later on.

315
00:25:38,411 --> 00:25:40,956
-Did you apply for the lab experience?
-Pardon?

316
00:25:46,253 --> 00:25:47,462
Let's eat.

317
00:25:48,797 --> 00:25:51,007
Have this too. Help yourself.

318
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:53,218
Thank you.

319
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:06,898
Sua may not be that different from me?

320
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:16,491
Hello, Woo-young.

321
00:26:17,993 --> 00:26:19,828
I'm on my way home now.

322
00:26:19,953 --> 00:26:20,787
Mi-rae.

323
00:26:25,292 --> 00:26:26,209
Good timing.

324
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:28,795
Hello.

325
00:26:30,005 --> 00:26:31,715
Can we talk for a minute?

326
00:26:32,882 --> 00:26:33,717
Sure.

327
00:26:34,134 --> 00:26:36,928
I noticed that you didn't apply.
Did you forget about it?

328
00:26:39,097 --> 00:26:40,015
No.

329
00:26:41,308 --> 00:26:44,144
I'm thinking of visiting my family
during summer break.

330
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:49,733
But it's not for the whole summer.
You can visit them after you're done.

331
00:26:52,485 --> 00:26:55,989
I thought you'd apply for sure
since you're interested in perfume.

332
00:26:56,531 --> 00:27:00,076
More importantly, I think it'd be a good
chance for you to find out whether

333
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:03,121
you are a good fit to pursue
a career in  the perfume industry.

334
00:27:05,081 --> 00:27:07,834
Also, there may not be another opportunity
to get hands-on experience

335
00:27:07,917 --> 00:27:10,378
at the perfume lab until you graduate.

336
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:17,761
Can I still apply for the program?

337
00:27:18,428 --> 00:27:20,639
Of course, I'll add your name to the list.

338
00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:25,018
-Shall we go?
-Yes.

339
00:27:27,354 --> 00:27:28,438
Woo-young.

340
00:27:31,274 --> 00:27:32,275
Thank you.

341
00:27:34,194 --> 00:27:36,696
Then are you free on Wednesday?

342
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:37,739
Pardon?

343
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:39,991
Let's watch a movie.
We can get a discount that day.

344
00:27:40,075 --> 00:27:43,495
Then I'll let Hyun-jung know as well.

345
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:46,247
Just the two of us.

346
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:50,085
I have something to tell you.

347
00:27:52,837 --> 00:27:53,713
Okay.

348
00:27:55,256 --> 00:27:56,091
Let's go.

349
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:06,017
I've gained a little bit of weight.

350
00:28:37,424 --> 00:28:38,466
Hey, wait.

351
00:28:42,637 --> 00:28:43,763
Hello, Dong-won.

352
00:28:45,765 --> 00:28:46,725
I heard that...

353
00:28:49,102 --> 00:28:52,480
canned tuna is high in sodium.
You shouldn't give it to cats.

354
00:28:52,564 --> 00:28:54,691
If you still want to,
you should rinse it in water first

355
00:28:54,774 --> 00:28:56,943
to remove the oil and sodium
before giving it to them.

356
00:28:58,778 --> 00:28:59,654
Hey, Sua.

357
00:29:00,613 --> 00:29:02,365
Oh, hi.

358
00:29:03,491 --> 00:29:05,118
-Did you eat?
-Yes, what about you?

359
00:29:05,285 --> 00:29:06,244
I ate as well.

360
00:29:18,047 --> 00:29:19,424
Hi, Mi-rae.

361
00:29:19,674 --> 00:29:21,301
-Hello.
-Hi.

362
00:29:22,469 --> 00:29:23,928
Let's sit over there.

363
00:29:24,345 --> 00:29:25,180
Hello.

364
00:29:25,889 --> 00:29:26,723
Hi.

365
00:29:29,934 --> 00:29:32,020
Do you guys still work there part-time?

366
00:29:32,896 --> 00:29:34,230
No, we quit.

367
00:29:34,814 --> 00:29:35,815
Even Kyung-seok?

368
00:29:36,691 --> 00:29:37,525
Yes.

369
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:42,572
Hello, Kyung-seok.

370
00:29:47,744 --> 00:29:49,704
I heard you quit the part-time job.

371
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:58,338
He shouldn't have been involved
in that thing. I feel bad for him.

372
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:11,601
Nice to meet you all.
I'm chief director, Lee Soo-hyun.

373
00:30:12,060 --> 00:30:14,979
This is Ms. Yun Soo-kyung, who will be
your guide through out the program.

374
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,357
Hello, nice to meet you all.

375
00:30:20,485 --> 00:30:22,529
While getting hands-on experience
at the lab,

376
00:30:22,612 --> 00:30:25,365
you'll learn about theories and history
of perfume.

377
00:30:25,448 --> 00:30:27,659
If you have any questions or suggestions,

378
00:30:27,742 --> 00:30:29,744
feel free to speak to Ms. Yun.

379
00:30:29,994 --> 00:30:31,287
-Okay.
-Okay.

380
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,083
Yes, come in.

381
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:40,129
Why did you come to school today?

382
00:30:40,255 --> 00:30:42,715
-I'm taking a summer class.
-Oh, I see.

383
00:30:43,466 --> 00:30:47,095
-What brings you here?
-There's something I want to tell you.

384
00:30:47,971 --> 00:30:48,888
To me?

385
00:30:49,973 --> 00:30:51,641
I'm not that eloquent,

386
00:30:51,724 --> 00:30:54,519
so I wrote down what I want to tell you.

387
00:31:05,989 --> 00:31:07,198
Okay. Bye.

388
00:31:18,793 --> 00:31:20,712
Dear Woo-young,

389
00:31:20,795 --> 00:31:23,172
I'm Kwon Yoon-byeol in sophomore year.

390
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:25,717
I have a crush on you.

391
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,011
You're very responsible
and have a strong sense of ethics.

392
00:31:28,094 --> 00:31:31,055
You respect women.
I like everything about you.

393
00:31:32,181 --> 00:31:35,393
I wrote this letter because I was too shy
to tell you in person.

394
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:38,354
Best regards, Kwon Yoon-byeol.

395
00:31:38,521 --> 00:31:40,523
Shy? She's so brave.

396
00:31:41,858 --> 00:31:43,860
Gosh, what should I do about this?

397
00:31:49,115 --> 00:31:51,492
First, go ahead and smell
the undiluted scents.

398
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:55,496
Then, please write down which scents
are in the perfume I gave you.

399
00:32:05,632 --> 00:32:08,927
Because I've been smelling
all these different scents

400
00:32:09,052 --> 00:32:10,470
I can't even smell anything.

401
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:13,389
You'll have to refresh your sense of smell
here and there.

402
00:32:13,473 --> 00:32:15,224
You can either take a break

403
00:32:15,308 --> 00:32:18,353
or try smelling coffee beans here.
It'll help as well.

404
00:32:41,542 --> 00:32:43,461
I think these scents are combined.

405
00:32:46,047 --> 00:32:48,967
Correct, you guessed every scent
in the perfume correctly.

406
00:32:51,427 --> 00:32:52,679
That's impressive.

407
00:32:52,762 --> 00:32:54,305
Are you Kang Mi-rae?

408
00:32:54,389 --> 00:32:56,349
You're the one who sent us
that perfume.

409
00:32:56,432 --> 00:33:00,353
Everyone in our lab loved that perfume.
We've been waiting to meet you in person.

410
00:33:01,062 --> 00:33:02,188
Thank you.

411
00:33:03,106 --> 00:33:05,650
You are a perfume expert.

412
00:33:28,423 --> 00:33:30,758
It didn't say it was going to rain.

413
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:38,516
Woo-young.

414
00:33:40,518 --> 00:33:41,561
Woo-young.

415
00:33:42,645 --> 00:33:44,063
Wait, Woo-young.

416
00:33:46,065 --> 00:33:47,650
What were you thinking about?

417
00:33:49,152 --> 00:33:50,611
Well, just some things.

418
00:33:53,614 --> 00:33:55,033
Did you eat dinner?

419
00:33:55,116 --> 00:33:58,161
Oh right, I didn't even have lunch today.

420
00:33:58,244 --> 00:34:00,913
You didn't eat all day?

421
00:34:01,330 --> 00:34:02,457
That's bad.

422
00:34:03,166 --> 00:34:04,375
Thanks for your concern.

423
00:34:07,795 --> 00:34:08,629
Well...

424
00:34:09,547 --> 00:34:12,341
Do you want to eat dinner with me?

425
00:34:13,134 --> 00:34:14,302
Sure, what should we eat?

426
00:34:15,511 --> 00:34:19,432
Since today is hot,
let's go somewhere close.

427
00:34:20,141 --> 00:34:21,100
-Sure.
-Okay.

428
00:34:26,355 --> 00:34:27,732
-Welcome.
-Hello.

429
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:29,484
-Hello.
-You can sit over there.

430
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:39,410
He's still here.

431
00:34:39,494 --> 00:34:41,954
He's a part-timer, not the owner.

432
00:34:42,038 --> 00:34:43,122
Oh really?

433
00:34:47,085 --> 00:34:49,087
-He must've gone bankrupt.
-Exactly.

434
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:50,755
You're here.

435
00:34:51,547 --> 00:34:52,715
What do you want? Beer?

436
00:34:54,842 --> 00:34:58,304
I don't think I'm good with perfume.
I can't even smell anything now.

437
00:34:58,387 --> 00:35:01,474
I liked it. I wasn't interested
in perfume, but it's really fun.

438
00:35:01,599 --> 00:35:03,392
-Right?
-Yes.

439
00:35:04,393 --> 00:35:07,730
Mi-rae, you look really interested.
You must really like perfume.

440
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:15,988
-I'm hungry.
-But you already ate.

441
00:35:16,114 --> 00:35:18,491
Why are you sitting here alone
like a loner?

442
00:35:19,575 --> 00:35:21,119
I was a loner all my life.

443
00:35:21,202 --> 00:35:22,995
What would you have done without me?

444
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:24,413
I know.

445
00:35:25,373 --> 00:35:26,499
Do you guys all want beer?

446
00:35:26,582 --> 00:35:27,667
-Beer sounds good.
-Great.

447
00:35:28,918 --> 00:35:31,212
Kyung-seok, what are you doing there?

448
00:35:32,296 --> 00:35:33,131
You should go.

449
00:35:33,798 --> 00:35:36,217
I can't be bothered.
I'm going to leave after this.

450
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:37,593
Hey, Kyung-seok.

451
00:35:38,136 --> 00:35:39,428
Get over here.

452
00:35:39,512 --> 00:35:40,680
Kyung-seok.

453
00:35:40,847 --> 00:35:42,974
-Come on.
-Come sit here.

454
00:35:43,099 --> 00:35:44,433
Please just go.

455
00:35:44,809 --> 00:35:46,811
You're practically volunteering
to become a loner.

456
00:35:47,395 --> 00:35:50,481
I thought things were getting better.
But you're doing this again.

457
00:35:52,567 --> 00:35:54,861
-Kyung-seok.
-Come quick.

458
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:57,530
Gosh, he's so cold-hearted.

459
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:08,499
Something wrong?

460
00:36:11,252 --> 00:36:12,753
No, there's something on my mind.

461
00:36:13,921 --> 00:36:14,755
What is it?

462
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:26,475
The thing is, someone confessed
that she likes me.

463
00:36:26,559 --> 00:36:27,393
What?

464
00:36:28,728 --> 00:36:29,854
Why are you so startled?

465
00:36:30,771 --> 00:36:31,689
Is it that shocking?

466
00:36:31,772 --> 00:36:33,774
No, it's not shocking.

467
00:36:34,609 --> 00:36:36,485
You're really popular.

468
00:36:36,569 --> 00:36:38,029
No, I'm not popular.

469
00:36:41,115 --> 00:36:42,491
What are you going to do?

470
00:36:44,619 --> 00:36:48,247
I'm just thinking about how
I'm going to turn her down.

471
00:36:50,708 --> 00:36:52,585
Have you already made up your mind?

472
00:36:52,668 --> 00:36:53,502
Yes.

473
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:57,340
I can't suddenly like someone
just because that person likes me.

474
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:02,011
You're very clear with what you want.

475
00:37:02,678 --> 00:37:04,764
I just know what kind of woman I like.

476
00:37:06,766 --> 00:37:08,643
Don't be too harsh though.

477
00:37:10,311 --> 00:37:14,523
Some people say you should be cold
when you reject someone.

478
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:17,360
But if she's a decent person,

479
00:37:17,944 --> 00:37:21,781
she'd appreciate it
if you reject her politely.

480
00:37:24,575 --> 00:37:25,534
You're right.

481
00:37:25,952 --> 00:37:31,874
I feel like it'll be a scar for life
if the guy she likes says harsh things.

482
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,920
I didn't experience it, but still.

483
00:37:37,129 --> 00:37:39,840
You understand even without experience
because you're a psych major.

484
00:37:43,469 --> 00:37:45,471
Isn't he good-looking?

485
00:37:46,138 --> 00:37:47,014
I'm not sure.

486
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:49,433
I think On Seung-woo is handsome.

487
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:52,144
I like guys who look cold-hearted.

488
00:37:53,854 --> 00:37:56,148
What about you, Sua?
Who's your favorite celebrity?

489
00:37:56,232 --> 00:37:57,066
Me?

490
00:37:57,692 --> 00:37:59,694
I don't know much about celebrities.

491
00:38:00,528 --> 00:38:02,113
I like guys who like me.

492
00:38:07,493 --> 00:38:08,744
What about you, Mi-rae?

493
00:38:09,203 --> 00:38:10,079
What?

494
00:38:10,830 --> 00:38:13,499
I've never heard you talk about guys.

495
00:38:14,583 --> 00:38:16,294
What kind of guys do you like?

496
00:38:20,548 --> 00:38:22,842
I haven't really thought about it.

497
00:38:23,843 --> 00:38:27,054
Do you like guys who treat you harshly?

498
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:29,598
You're the first girl
to treat me this way.

499
00:38:29,765 --> 00:38:30,599
Or...

500
00:38:30,683 --> 00:38:33,227
Let me become your firefighter.

501
00:38:33,311 --> 00:38:34,729
Do you like guys who are warm?

502
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:36,147
Which do you prefer?

503
00:38:36,731 --> 00:38:38,941
I just like the normal type of guys.

504
00:38:40,234 --> 00:38:42,445
What's the standard of normal?

505
00:38:42,528 --> 00:38:44,113
This is so frustrating.

506
00:38:44,196 --> 00:38:46,866
Let's just say you don't have
an ideal type.

507
00:38:49,452 --> 00:38:50,995
I like warm-hearted guys.

508
00:38:51,078 --> 00:38:53,789
-I'm going to leave.
-Kyung-seok.

509
00:38:54,373 --> 00:38:56,125
See you, Kyung-seok.

510
00:38:57,501 --> 00:38:58,669
Bye.

511
00:38:58,753 --> 00:39:01,422
It seems like he's becoming
more harsh.

512
00:39:02,465 --> 00:39:04,467
It's bothering me.

513
00:39:34,163 --> 00:39:35,331
Take this.

514
00:39:35,414 --> 00:39:37,375
It might start raining again.

515
00:39:41,504 --> 00:39:42,880
Okay.

516
00:39:43,839 --> 00:39:45,841
-Thank you.
